Includes overview of psychopathology, aetiology, diagnosis, possibilities of treatment and prevention of mental disorders. Study course consists of two modules clinical psychology and psychiatryObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide knowledge of the prevalence, aetiology, pathogenesis, symptoms, course, assessment, treatment as well as service organisation and possibilities for prevention of major mental disorders.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion the student:  - knows contemporary research results of the prevalence and factors affecting the risk, causes and course of mental disorders; - knows the psychological models of mental and psychosomatic disorders, and is able to explain the cognitive models of anxiety and psychosomatic disorders; - knows theories of stress - knows the diagnostic criteria of common mental disorders; - is able to collect information about patient's symptoms, history of mental disorders and life history;  - can explore and describe the mental status of patients; is able to recognise psychiatric conditions requiring emergency treatment; - knows the methods and aims of psychological assessment in different medical settings; - knows the possibilities of prevention, evidence based treatment and service organisation of mental disorders, knows the treatment principles and guidelines of major mental disorders; - understands the nature of evidence-based psychotherapy and knows the major schools of psychotherapy; - knows the principles of interpersonal communication, and is acquainted with skills supporting the interaction with the partner; - is able to use interviewing skills, including skills for active listening; - can impart information in a manner that enables patients to promote their health; - knows laws that regulate the treatment and rehabilitation of persons with mental disorders; - knows the ethical principles of working with people and problematic relationships that may arise in helping professions; - understands the nature and contributing factors of professional burnout; - knows the specific psychological features of working with children.
